  "grammarNote": {
    "title": "Extended Negation: ne...plus, ne...rien",
    "explanation": "Perrault n'est plus là. — he is no LONGER there. On n'entend plus rien. — we hear NOTHING anymore.\n\nBeyond ne...pas, French has ne...plus (no longer) and ne...rien (nothing). Two negation words wrap the verb.\n\nRe-read and find every ne...plus and ne...rien. What has stopped? What is absent?"
